<dl>
  <dt class="expand">Class 02 (January 13, 2023): Thoughts on
    Language/Power, Further Bag of Words Exploration, Introduction to
    Python</dt>  
  <div class="collapse"><dd>
      <p>Before class</p>
      <ul><li>Read the following articles:
	  <ol>
	    <li><a href="https://the.ink/p/kamala-versus-daenerys"
		   target="_blank">Mayflower Mouth</a>,
	      by <a href="http://www.anand.ly/" target="_blank">Anand
		Giridharadas</a>.</li> 
	    <li><a href="https://www.wbur.org/onlyagame/2020/06/26/racial-stereotypes-sports-broadcast-bias"
	    target="_blank">'Crafty' Vs. 'Sneaky': How Racial Bias In Sports
	    Broadcasting Hurts Everyone</a>, by Karen Given, broadcast on
	    WBUR, 27 June 2020. Based on
	    <a href="https://scholarworks.utrgv.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=1013&context=soc_fac"
	    target="_blank">research</a> by
	    <a href="https://twitter.com/SociologistRay" target="_blank">Rashawn Ray</a> and
	      <a href="https://liberalarts.tamu.edu/sociology/profile/steven-foy/#:~:text=Steven%20Foy%20is%20an%20Associate,colorism%2C%20and%20mental%20health)."
	      target="_blank">Steven Foy</a>.</li>
	    <li><a href="https://openlab.citytech.cuny.edu/fywpd/files/2020/02/OneCorrectWay.pdf"
	    target="_blank">There is one Correct Way of Writing and
	    Speaking</a>, by Anjali Pattanayak, in
	    <a href="https://textbooks.lib.wvu.edu/badideas/badideasaboutwriting-book.pdf"
	    target="_blank">Bad Ideas about Writing</a>, Edited by
	    Cheryl E. Ball & Drew M. Loewe, West Virginia University Libraries, 2017.</li> 
	</ol>
	<li>Possible discussion questions:
	  <ul>
	    <li>What, if anything, particulary resonated with
	      you?</li>
	    <li>What questions do you have about the readings?</li>
	    <li>What are some questions or topics you'd like to
	    discuss as a class?</li>
	  </ul></li>
	</ul>
      <p>In-class content</p>
      <ul>
	<li>Discuss Reading </li>
	<li>Experiment and explore with words in bags</li>
	<li>Introduction to python</li>
      </ul>
    </dd>
  </div>
</dl>

